Citation.sTitle: Thermodynamic and Acoustic Properties of 1,3-Dibromopropane and 1,5-Dibromopentane within the Temperature Range From 293K to 313K at Pressures up to 100MPa
Citation.sAbstract: This study reports new experimental data of the speed of sound in liquid 1,3-dibromopropane and 1,5-dibromopentane from 293K to 313K at pressures up to 101MPa, measured with a pulse echo overlap method. The experimental results have been used to calculate densities, isobaric heat capacities, isobaric coefficient of thermal expansion, and isentropic and isothermal compressibilities as functions of temperature and pressure.
